My work was fastening down the things on the deck so that nothing could roll about if the weather should grow rough when we got further from the land.
Jip was up in the peak of the boat with ears cocked and nose stuck outâlike a statue, so stillâhis keen old eyes keeping a sharp look-out for floating wrecks, sand-bars, and other dangers.
Each one of us had some special job to do, part of the proper running of a ship.
