We divided the twenty-four hours of the day into three spells; and we took it in turns to sleep our eight hours and be awake sixteen.
So the ship was well looked after, with two of us always on duty.
Besides that, Polynesia, who was an older sailor than any of us, and really knew a lot about running ships, seemed to be always awakeâexcept when she took her couple of winks in the sun, standing on one leg beside the wheel.
