âWhat discourteous pagans!
â said Bumpo.
âDid you ever see such inhospitability?
âNever even asked us if weâd had breakfast, the benighted bounders!
â
âSh!
Theyâre going off to their village,â said Polynesia.
âIâll bet thereâs a village on the other side of those mountains.
If you take my advice, Doctor, youâll get away from this beach while their backs are turned.
