â
âYes,â sighed Polynesia, shaking the rain off her feathers, âthis is England all rightâYou can tell it by the beastly climate.
â
âOh, but fellows,â cried Jip, as he sniffed up the air in great gulps, âit has a _smell_âa good and glorious smell!
âExcuse me a minute: I see a water-rat.
â
âSh!
âListen!
â said Chee-Chee through teeth that chattered with the cold.
